                       "committer":  {
                                         "name":  "drhalilmurattasci",
                                         "email":  "drhalilmurattasci@users.noreply.github.com",
                                         "date":  "2026-06-01T21:25:00Z"
                                     },
                       "message":  "MENUBAR-FILE-WIRING: shell drains the menu FIFO + routes Command one-way (Dispatch B)\n\nFrontier step 3, Dispatch B of 2 — the shell-side wiring over the #287 host\nsubstrate. The File menu is now FUNCTIONAL end-to-end: editor-shell drains the\nhost\u0027s MenuCommandHandoff and routes each Command one-way into the existing\nOpen/Save/Save-As handlers. editor-shell only (+ the auto Cargo.lock dep-edge\nrecord).\n\n- crates/editor-shell/Cargo.toml: add rge-editor-ui — the canonical menu Command\n  vocabulary, declared directly (a real semantic dependency, NOT hidden behind a\n  host re-export). editor-shell + editor-ui are both Tier-2; forbidden-dep rule 4\n  restricts editor-ui\u0027s OUTGOING deps only, so editor-shell -\u003e editor-ui is\n  permitted (validated explicitly before the gate: `[forbidden-dep] PASS (0\n  violations)`).\n- lifecycle/mod.rs: `menu_command_handoff: Option\u003cArc\u003cMenuCommandHandoff\u003e\u003e` field\n  (None in all 3 constructors); MenuCommandHandoff added to the egui-host import.\n- render_path.rs: retain the handoff Arc in init_render_state (beside the other\n  two handoffs); new `pub(crate) fn drain_and_route_menu_commands` clones the\n  Arc, drains FIFO, and matches Command::{OpenFile,Save,SaveAs} -\u003e the existing\n  handle_open_request / handle_save_request / handle_save_as_new_project_request\n  (any other Command is logged + ignored). Called at the TOP of render_frame (the\n  sole redraw entry, which early-returns render_frame_egui_only for the Phase-1\n  path, so one drain covers both render paths) — BEFORE this frame\u0027s\n  surface/window/encoder borrows are taken, so the \u0026mut self handler calls don\u0027t\n  contend with a live \u0026self borrow; it processes the prior frame\u0027s enqueued\n  commands and the host\u0027s continuous request_redraw renders any resulting swap.\n- lifecycle/tests.rs: 4 SEPARATE per-command route tests — Open swaps the world,\n  Save invokes the writer + marks saved, SaveAs adopts a Project source, an\n  unrouted Undo is a no-op — reusing the existing mock hooks.\n\nRouting is one-way into existing handlers (NO new command enum, no handler\nreimplementation); the handlers own their PIE gating, so a menu Save during Play\nno-ops in the handler. Command::SaveAs routes to\nhandle_save_as_new_project_request (the File item is labelled \"Save As New\nProject\"), per the #287 substrate contract. pub(crate) on the helper so the\nsibling tests.rs module can drive it.\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints (forbidden-dep green WITH the new edge).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
