                       "message":  "MENUBAR-FILE-WIRING: correction — fix 2 stale menu-drain timing comments (#288)\n\nCodex NEEDS_CORRECTION (comments only). When EXEC relocated the drain (borrow\nfix: after-host.render -\u003e top-of-render_frame), two CHANGED comments were left\ndescribing the OLD timing:\n- crates/editor-shell/Cargo.toml:34: \"after `EguiHost::render`\" -\u003e \"at the top of\n  each redraw frame\".\n- crates/editor-shell/src/lifecycle/mod.rs:669-670: \"Drained each frame AFTER\n  `EguiHost::render` by\" -\u003e \"Drained at the TOP of each `render_frame` (before\n  this frame\u0027s render borrows) by\".\n\nrender_path.rs (the helper doc + the top-of-render_frame call-site comment) was\nalready correct from EXEC. A whole-change-set re-grep for the old timing phrasing\nnow returns nothing stale.\n\nComments only; no code / test change. The implementation + the 4 route tests\nstand.\n\nGate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
